commit.message:
Ensure timeout is used on Python 2.7

_create_socket isn't used with the Python 2 version of imaplib so the
open method has been overrided to make it consistent across Python
version.

Fixes #380.

Use ptpython for interactive shell if available

Closes #272

Fix invalid string escape sequences

These were causing DeprecationWarnings in Python 3.7 and later.

Fixes #397.

Prevent UnicodeDecodeError in IMAPlibLoggerAdapter

Under Python 2.7, some log messages arrive as bytes and if these
contain non-ASCII characters a UnicodeDecodeError could occur due to
implicit conversions when msg was examined.

Now a best-efforts unicode conversion is done to prevent this.

Fixes #367.

Prevent converting numbers with leading zeroes to int. (#390) (#405)

* Prevent converting numbers with leading zeroes to int.
* But do treat a single 0 as an int.

commit.message:
Fix useless ref cycle in lexer

Remove a useless ref cycle in LiteralHandlingIter. This helps the ref
count based garbage collection in CPython.

Previously it was failing with the following exception when a default attribute
was set to None.
